We added a new option `defaultTriggerBreakpoint` to the `addTriggeredBreakpoint` function. This option is set to the first breakpoint in the `triggerBreakpoints` array, or `null` if the array is empty. We then register a command to set the default trigger breakpoint when the "Add Triggered Breakpoint" dialog is opened.

